  "body": "A few of our users have reported this issue and I also have ran into it. Currently the beacon node doesn't have the ability to switch from recursive parent syncing back to initial sync. My beacon node is at a state where says initial sync exited at `224224` and it starts to requesting parent block at `224867`.  With 600 slots differences we should be able to switch back to initial sync \r\n\r\n```\r\n[2019-12-12 14:01:22]  INFO initial-sync: Synced up to slot 224224\r\n[2019-12-12 14:01:32]  INFO sync: Requesting parent block currentSlot=224867 parentRoot=aab0b373b671ebd71f8b9c6dad406c6725e390aa34be03f99f346f3387cf3b9c\r\n```",
